(Regex To DFA Project - Step By Step Code Explanation) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. PROJECT GOAL) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This project converts a regular expression into a working minimized DFA. It is designed) Tj
T*
(as a university Formal Languages and Automata Theory project, so the code is separated) Tj
T*
(into small classes and the console menu is easy to present.) Tj
T*
(The full path is: user input regex -> validation and postfix conversion -> Thompson NFA) Tj
T*
(-> subset DFA -> minimized DFA -> string testing.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. SUPPORTED REGEX RULES) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The user may enter normal symbols such as a, b, 0, and 1. The operator | means union, *) Tj
T*
(means zero or more, + means one or more, ? means optional, and parentheses group) Tj
T*
(expressions.) Tj
T*
(Concatenation is implicit. For example, ab means a followed by b. The program inserts an) Tj
T*
(internal dot operator only after validation. The user can write # for epsilon.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3. MAIN.JAVA) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Main.java contains only the main method. It creates a UI object and calls start\(\). This) Tj
T*
(keeps the program entry point simple and easy to explain.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4. UI.JAVA) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(UI.java owns the console menu. Option 1 lets the user enter any regex. Options 2, 3, and) Tj
T*
(4 display the NFA, DFA, and minimized DFA. Option 5 tests custom strings. Option 6 runs) Tj
T*
(the professor demo test case.) Tj
T*
(When a regex is entered, UI resets state numbering, calls RegexParser, builds the NFA,) Tj
T*
(converts it to DFA, minimizes it, and stores all results so they can be displayed later.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(5. REGEXPARSER.JAVA) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(RegexParser validates the expression before any automaton is built. It checks empty) Tj
T*
(input, wrong operator positions, missing operands, and unbalanced parentheses.) Tj
T*
(After validation, it inserts explicit concatenation internally. Example: ab becomes a.b.) Tj
T*
(Then it uses the shunting-yard algorithm to convert infix regex into postfix regex,) Tj
T*
(because Thompson construction is easier on postfix input.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(6. STATE.JAVA AND NFA.JAVA) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(State.java represents one NFA state. Each state has an id such as q0 and a map of) Tj
T*
(transitions. A transition maps one symbol to a set of target states, because an NFA can) Tj
T*
(have many choices for the same symbol.) Tj
T*
(NFA.java stores the start state, final states, all states, and alphabet. It also prints) Tj
T*
(a readable list of transitions for presentation.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(7. THOMPSONCONSTRUCTION.JAVA) Tj
