() Tj
T*
(ThompsonConstruction builds small NFA fragments and combines them. For a normal symbol,) Tj
T*
(it creates two states with one transition between them.) Tj
T*
(For concatenation, final states of the left fragment connect by epsilon to the start of) Tj
T*
(the right fragment. For union, a new start branches by epsilon to both fragments and) Tj
T*
(both fragments connect to a new final state.) Tj
T*
(For star, plus, and optional, the class adds epsilon transitions according to the formal) Tj
T*
(definitions of those operators.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(8. SUBSETCONSTRUCTION.JAVA) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(SubsetConstruction converts the NFA to a DFA. Each DFA state is a set of NFA states. The) Tj
T*
(first DFA state is epsilon-closure of the NFA start state.) Tj
T*
(For each DFA state and each alphabet symbol, the program applies move\(\), then) Tj
T*
(epsilonClosure\(\). If that set has not appeared before, a new DFA state is created.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(9. DFASTATE.JAVA AND DFA.JAVA) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(DFAState.java stores the set of NFA states represented by one DFA state. It also stores) Tj
T*
(whether the DFA state is final.) Tj
T*
(DFA.java stores all DFA states, alphabet, start state, and final states. It prints a) Tj
T*
(transition table and marks start states with -> and final states with *.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(10. DFAMINIMIZER.JAVA) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(DFAMinimizer uses partition refinement. It first separates final states from non-final) Tj
T*
(states. Then it repeatedly splits groups whose transitions go to different groups.) Tj
T*
(When no group can be split again, each group becomes one state in the minimized DFA. A) Tj
T*
(trap state is added internally when needed to complete missing transitions.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(11. STRINGTESTER.JAVA) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(StringTester starts at the minimized DFA start state. For every input character, it) Tj
T*
(follows exactly one transition. If the final state after the whole string is a DFA final) Tj
T*
(state, the string is accepted.) Tj
T*
(It also prints a trace such as D0 --a--> D1 so the professor can see how the input was) Tj
T*
(processed.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(12. PROFESSOR DEMO) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Menu option 6 runs this regex: \(a|b\)*abb. The language is all strings over {a,b} that) Tj
T*
(end with abb.) Tj
T*
(Expected accepted strings: abb, aabb, bababb. Expected rejected strings: ab, aba, bbb.) Tj
T*
(After the demo runs, the minimized DFA remains loaded, so the user can choose option 5) Tj
T*
(and enter any custom test string.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(13. HOW TO RUN) Tj
T*
() Tj
